<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-11-20T05:24:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-11-20T05:24:00-05:00" n="79" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89 Latvia/31: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">White</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-11-20T12:00:00+01:36"><hi rend="italic">November 20,
                                        1924—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 1:24
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>183. Minister of Finance has informed me that the Cabinet of Ministers
                            has decided to inaugurate funding negotiations through the Latvian
                            consul at New York.<note n="6" xml:id="d79fn6">Minister Coleman informed
                                the Department by despatch of Jan. 28, 1925, that Mr. Ringold
                                Kalning, formerly Latvian Minister of Finance, would proceed to the
                                United States as Commissioner to assist the consul in the funding
                                negotiations (file no. 800.51 W 89 Latvia/36).</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>